<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!--
  labwc config for the Pi kiosk.

  The <touch> rule deliberately has NO deviceName: it applies to ALL touch
  devices. This is the durable fix for swipe-to-scroll on a touchscreen kiosk.

  Why no deviceName: a DSI touch panel often enumerates with a name like
  "11-0038 generic ft5x06 (NN)" whose "(NN)" suffix is assigned by libinput and
  CHANGES across reboots/re-enumeration. Pinning an exact name means the rule
  silently stops matching after a reboot. Matching all touch devices avoids that.

  mouseEmulation="yes": touch acts as a mouse, so there's a visible cursor and
  taps register as clicks. (mouseEmulation="no" delivers native wl_touch but
  removes the cursor entirely, and Chromium's wl_touch scrolling proved
  unreliable on this labwc build.) Swipe-to-scroll is therefore handled in the
  web app itself (a press-and-drag scroll handler that works with the emulated
  mouse), not by the compositor.

  mapToOutput="DSI-2" -> map touch coordinates to the panel; change this to your
  output name (see `wlr-randr`) if your display isn't "DSI-2".

  Install to ~/.config/labwc/rc.xml on the Pi; a reboot (or full labwc restart)
  is required for touch-input config to take effect — a live SIGHUP reconfigure
  does NOT re-apply it.
-->
<openbox_config xmlns="http://openbox.org/3.4/rc">
  <touch mapToOutput="DSI-2" mouseEmulation="yes"/>
</openbox_config>
